Ranchland News
August 31 at 5:33 PM Â·

A new 4-year course of education started recently at Calhan High School. It is the brainchild of Heidi Sellers who is the schoolâ€™s agriculture instructor and FFA advisor. The program, called Agricultural Education, has three pathways, including horticulture science, animal production and ag power structure and technical systems. The last track is a rapidly growing segment of agriculture, says Sellers. It includes advocating for agriculture.

Picture 1: Sadie Taylor, Sophie Waugh, Dale Drew, Natalie Hlatki, Kaitlyn Armes, Ethan Parker, Antone Sellers and Wyatt Chamblin pose in front of the greenhouses used in their class.

Picture 2: Natalie Hlatki shows off her tomato plant.

Picture 3: Wyatt Chamblin demonstrates the composter used in the horticulture class.

post_text: iPad rollouts for 20/21 School Year for Middle School and High School Students are July 27th through July 31st from 8-4 daily. It is vital for all Middle School and High School students to come and get their devices during this time. The 1-1 Agreement must be completed (digitally), the Handbook Agreement form must be completed (digitally), and a $50 insurance fee must be paid before a student can receive their device. Please take the time to read through the 1-1 Agreement; it contains essential information. All documents can be found in the respective school sites under the "Our Schools" tab.

Calhan Preschool enrollment packets for the 2020-2021 school year are now available! If interested, packets may be picked up from the front office at 800 Bulldog Drive or call 719-347-2766 to request a packet be mailed to you.

For further assistance, please contact Sharon Rotenberry at sharon.rotenberry@calhanschool.org or Jennifer Hart at jhart@calhanschool.org.

post_text: As the country, the state and El Paso County navigate recent public health issues resulting from concerns surrounding the Coronavirus (COVID-19), please know that the Calhan School District is committed to doing everything we can to keep your children safe, and our community informed. With that goal in mind, we will post current updates from public health agencies, and updated district-specific information on this page. This page will be updated daily during school days.

post_text: The Eldon Glaser Memorial Scholarship will award one $500 scholarship to a graduating senior planning to attend college or university after graduation.
